cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.PF, cs.SE, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the scheduling of parallel loops in OpenMP programs, which is a topic related to parallel computing and programming languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes two competing interfaces for user-defined scheduling, which is related to programming language design and implementation, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely category. The paper also discusses the interfaces in the context of C, C++, and Fortran, which suggests cs.PF (Performance) as a possible category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new feature for the OpenMP standard, which is related to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed interfaces, which is related to computer architecture, making cs.AR (Computer Architecture) a less likely but still possible category.
